class Solution {
    public int largestInteger(int num) {
        char[] s = Integer.toString(num).toCharArray();
        int n = s.length;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
            for (int j = i + 1; j < n; ++j) {
                if ((s[i] - s[j]) % 2 == 0 && s[i] < s[j]) {
                    char tmp = s[i];
                    s[i] = s[j];
                    s[j] = tmp;
                }
            }
        }
        return Integer.parseInt(new String(s));
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(d^2) where d is the number of digits
space complexity: O(d)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Convert the number to a char array, then greedily bubble the largest digit of the same parity to each position via adjacent swaps. The quadratic scan is fast because the digit count is capped at 10.

